17. Epicurei, the followers of Epicurus, He established his philosophie school in the celebrated ‘ Garden of Epicurus ’ st Athens. Though he held that pleasure was the chief good, his mode of life was simple and temperate. ‘Pleasure' with him really consisted in pure and noble mental enjoyment‚ in freedom from pain and from all influences which disturb our peace of mind.
